			  	how about this (note: i'm still going to fix the bug), make privateering more usefull for gaining some exp.<br />
<br />
for example, i'm currently testing this system:<br />
You privateer a person like normal, it goes through the planets randomly like normal trying to privateer, when you privateer a planet it calculates how much PP you CAN steal and carry base on the number of ships and their size/class with up to 100% of the planets pp per turn. you then gain a base of 50% of that amount, then it adds or subtracts to that 50% based on your commies attributes (especially privateering ability) for a gain of up to 100% of that amount (possibly 100% of the planets pp per turn for that turn. your commie than GAINS 1% of the PP stolen or at least 250exp.<br />
doing this on someone with alot of URs and as say, a buckaneer, you could possibly gain 1mil+ per planet, make your enemy lose that for that turn, and gain 10k exp per planet (not bad imo). and you don't lose fleets. well, unless they station and you get detected and such. not this is still just a testing system that will probably change and such.<br />
<br />
there is also a proposed &quot;bounty&quot; system. where players relationships with the empire can cause them to become bounties, then other players can attack (to a certain extent) them for empire favor and commander exp and possibly planets.			   <P align=right></P>
